'''Anthropic''' is an American [[artificial intelligence]] (AI) [[Startup company|startup]] and [[Benefit corporation|public-benefit corporation]], founded by former members of [[OpenAI]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=ChatGPT must be regulated and A.I. ‘can be used by bad actors,’ warns OpenAI’s CTO |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/artificial-intelligence-must-regulated-warns-204546351.html |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=finance.yahoo.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Vincent |first=James |date=2023-02-03 |title=Google invested $300 million in AI firm founded by former OpenAI researchers |url=https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/3/23584540/google-anthropic-investment-300-million-openai-chatgpt-rival-claude |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=The Verge |language=en-US}}</ref> Anthropic specializes in developing [[General artificial intelligence|general AI systems]] and [[large language model|language model]]s, with a company ethos of [[Ethics of artificial intelligence|responsible AI]] usage. Since late 2022, [[Google]] has invested nearly $400 million in the company, with Anthropic announcing a formal partnership with [[Google Cloud Platform|Google Cloud]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-02-03 |title=Google Invests Almost $400 Million in ChatGPT Rival Anthropic |language=en |work=Bloomberg.com |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-02-03/google-invests-almost-400-million-in-ai-startup-anthropic |access-date=2023-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-03 |title=Google invests $300 million in Anthropic as race to compete with ChatGPT heats up |url=https://venturebeat.com/ai/google-invests-300-million-in-anthropic-as-race-to-compete-with-chatgpt-heats-up/ |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=VentureBeat |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-04 |title=Google invests nearly $400 million in ChatGPT rival Anthropic: Report |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/google-invests-nearly-400-million-in-chatgpt-rival-anthropic-report-11675502627352.html |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=mint |language=en}}</ref>

== History ==
Anthropic was founded in 2021 by former senior members of OpenAI, principally siblings Daniela Amodei and Dario Amodei, the latter of whom served as OpenAI's Vice President of Research.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Papadopoulos |first=Loukia |date=2023-02-05 |title=Google invests $400 million in Anthropic to battle the power of ChatGPT |url=https://interestingengineering.com/innovation/google-invests-anthropic-battle-chatgpt |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=interestingengineering.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=OpenAI Is Making Headlines. It’s Also Seeding Talent Across Silicon Valley |url=https://www.theinformation.com/articles/openai-is-making-headlines-its-also-seeding-talent-across-silicon-valley |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=The Information}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Daniela and Dario Amodei on Anthropic |url=https://futureoflife.org/podcast/daniela-and-dario-amodei-on-anthropic/ |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=Future of Life Institute |language=en-US}}</ref> The Amodei siblings were among others who left OpenAI due to directional differences, specifically regarding OpenAI's ventures with [[Microsoft]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-07 |title=As Anthropic seeks billions to take on OpenAI, ‘industrial capture’ is nigh. Or is it? |url=https://venturebeat.com/ai/as-anthropic-seeks-billions-to-take-on-openai-industrial-capture-is-nigh-or-is-it/ |access-date=2023-05-24 |website=VentureBeat |language=en-US}}</ref> In February 2023, Anthropic was sued by Texas-based Anthrop LLC for use of their registered trademark "Anthropic A.I."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Setty |first=Riddhi  |date=2023-02-23 |title=Anthropic A.I. Sues AI Company for Trademark Infringement|url=https://news.bloomberglaw.com/ip-law/anthropic-a-i-sues-ai-company-for-trademark-infringement |access-date=2023-02-23 |website=Bloomberg Law |language=en-US}}</ref>

== Projects ==

=== Claude ===
Consisting of former researchers involved in OpenAI's [[ChatGPT]],{{Citation needed|date=April 2023}} Anthropic began development on its own AI [[chatbot]], named Claude.<ref>{{Cite web |title=ChatGPT must be regulated and A.I. ‘can be used by bad actors,’ warns OpenAI’s CTO |url=https://fortune.com/2023/02/05/artificial-intelligence-must-be-regulated-chatgpt-openai-cto-mira-murati/ |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=Fortune |language=en}}</ref> Similar to ChatGPT, Claude uses a messaging interface where users can submit questions or requests and receive highly detailed and relevant responses.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Meet Claude: Anthropic’s Rival to ChatGPT {{!}} Blog {{!}} Scale AI |url=https://scale.com/blog/chatgpt-vs-claude |access-date=2023-02-06 |website=ScaleAI}}</ref>

Initially available in closed beta through a [[Slack (software)|Slack]] integration, Claude is now accessible to users via the [[Poe (chatbot)|Poe]] app by [[Quora]] along with two other chatbots. The app is currently available for [[iOS]] and will soon be available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]].<ref>{{Cite web  |date=2023-02-06 |title=Quora opens its new AI chatbot app Poe to the general public |url=https://techcrunch.com/2023/02/06/quora-opens-its-new-ai-chatbot-app-poe-to-the-general-public/ |access-date=2023-02-19 |website=TechCrunch |language=en-US}}</ref>

=== Interpretability research ===
Anthropic also publishes research on the [[interpretability (machine learning)|interpretability]] of machine learning systems, focusing on the [[Transformer (machine learning model)|transformer]] architecture.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transformer Circuits Thread |url=https://transformer-circuits.pub/ |access-date=2023-02-09 |website=transformer-circuits.pub}}</ref>

